Five suspects have been confirmed dead, two civilians shot and two injured following an attempted Cash-in-Transit (CIT) robbery in Springfield Park and a gun-battle between police and robbers that ended in Parlock, a short while ago. Police acted swiftly.According to reports, both areas have been cordoned off as they are active scenes and all relevant police personnel are on site.Rescue Care s Garrith Jamieson said, Four civilians have been treated off Parlock Drive where a vehicle crashed and a gunfight broken out between SAPS and suspects. Two seriously injured civilians were shot and two minor injuries. Police investigations are underway.